# Order Intelligence Layer — local environment template.
#
# Copy to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in real values:
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# `.env` is loaded on import by ai_service/settings.py (python-dotenv), and only
# fills variables NOT already set in the real environment — so shell exports and
# container/CI env vars still take precedence. Never commit a real `.env`.

# --- Azure AI Foundry — leave blank to run in LLM-fallback mode ---------------
# With these unset/blank, the AI service still runs: explanations/routing/
# summaries take the fallback path (source="fallback"). Fill them to enable the
# real LLM (source="ai") — no code change needed.
#
# Model recommendation (Azure AI Foundry, OpenAI GPT-5 family):
#   * EXPLAINER + ROUTER -> gpt-5.4-nano  (lightest/cheapest, low-latency; these
#     are the high-frequency calls — 2 per WARN/ERROR log. Nano is plenty: the
#     router output is enum-validated in nodes.py, so a small model is safe.)
#   * SUMMARY            -> gpt-5.4-mini  (runs rarely — once per completed
#     journey — so the small step up in capability costs almost nothing.)
#   Simplest option: gpt-5.4-nano for all three. (nano/mini need no registration;
#   full gpt-5 does.) Set the values below to the DEPLOYMENT names in your Foundry
#   resource (a deployment name is chosen at deploy time — not the model id).

# ENDPOINT: paste either the Foundry project endpoint (".../api/projects/<name>")
#   or the OpenAI-compatible service URL (".../openai/v1"). The code normalizes a
#   project endpoint to the /openai/v1 form, which is what accepts the API key
#   below (the raw project endpoint requires Entra ID auth, not a key).
#AZURE_AI_FOUNDRY_ENDPOINT=
#AZURE_AI_FOUNDRY_API_KEY=
# API_VERSION: leave as "preview" (the GA v1 rolling version). A dated value like
#   2024-12-01-preview is rejected with 400 "API version not supported".
#AZURE_AI_FOUNDRY_API_VERSION=preview
#AZURE_AI_FOUNDRY_DEPLOYMENT_EXPLAINER=
#AZURE_AI_FOUNDRY_DEPLOYMENT_ROUTER=
#AZURE_AI_FOUNDRY_DEPLOYMENT_SUMMARY=

# --- Infrastructure (defaults match docker-compose.yml; override if needed) ---
# ES_URL=http://localhost:9200
# REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0
# RABBITMQ_URL=amqp://guest:guest@localhost:5672/
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://oil:oil@localhost:5432/oil

# --- Full-Docker run (`docker compose --profile app up`) ----------------------
# Only needed to run the whole stack in containers (see CLAUDE.md "Running").
# NPM_TOKEN: a GitHub Packages read token — REQUIRED to build the dashboard
#   image (it installs the private @computacenter-ro/style-guide package). The
#   backend/Python services do NOT need it. Without it, `--profile app up` fails
#   at the dashboard build step only.
# NPM_TOKEN=
# POSTGRES_USER / _PASSWORD / _DB default to oil/oil/oil (compose); keep in sync
#   with DATABASE_URL if you change them.
# POSTGRES_USER=oil
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=oil
# POSTGRES_DB=oil

# --- Poller / journey tuning (optional; shown with their defaults) ------------
# POLL_INTERVAL=10
# WINDOW_START_OFFSET=25
# WINDOW_END_OFFSET=5
# STALLED_TIMEOUT=90

# --- Teams webhooks (backend [5]; unset => cards print to stdout) -------------
# TEAMS_WEBHOOK_NETWORKING=
# TEAMS_WEBHOOK_DEVOPS=
# TEAMS_WEBHOOK_BACKEND=
# TEAMS_WEBHOOK_DATABASE=
# TEAMS_WEBHOOK_GENERAL=
